 TechOps
 31-Aug-2021
 Ref #:  9142 How you'll help us Keep Climbing (overview & key responsibilities)
 The PTE team at Delta TechOps develops and supports predictive technologies and digital solutions across multiple airframe and engine types. Predictive Technology Engineering is seeking a data scientist with a primary focus on the development and support of predictive, artificial intelligence (AI) and machine learning (ML) solutions. The position requires a proven track record in machine learning, statistical analysis, and data story telling. Ideally, the individual has experience and proven record of success on using data to shift from condition-based maintenance practices to predictive maintenance strategies in operational environments. The individual should have excellent organizational and communication skills and feel comfortable in a fast-paced environment. The role will support the delivery of digital transformation at Delta Air Lines. Develop machine learning solutions for complex business problems (large network based environment) Coordinate with Engineering, Technical Specialists, and Developers to create, validate and connect predictive model to Predictive UI/UX Modeling of complex systems and predictive analytics to provide alerting of impending failures of components and or systems based on downloaded aircraft sensor data
 What you need to succeed (minimum qualifications)
 Bachelor's degree in Statistics, Engineering, Mathematics, or Computer Science or related quantitative degrees with graduate level education in Data Science, Statistics, Mathematics, Operations Research, or equivalent combination of education and experience (Hive/Hadoop/Spark) required Strong written, oral communication and interpersonal skills Strong project management, organizational, and prioritizations skills Must be able to interact and collaborate at all levels, cross-divisional working groups, and outside entities Embraces diverse people, thinking and styles.
 
Where permitted by applicable law, must have received or be willing to receive the COVID-19 vaccine by date of hire to be considered for U.S.-based job, if not currently employed by Delta Air Lines, Inc. What will give you a competitive edge (preferred qualifications) (Master's and PhDs preferred) Proficiency in working with relational databases (SQL) Proficiency in Machine Learning techniques (Python, SciKit Learn, R, SAS and other machine learning platform) Proficiency in deep learning technique/platform (TensorFlow, Keras, PyTorch) Working knowledge of Reinforcement Learning preferred Working knowledge of distributed computing platforms. Working knowledge of API Consumption preferred Working knowledge of Alteryx, Tableau, Hyperion preferred < Go back Delta Airlines 14 days ago original job Report job You must create an Indeed account before continuing to the company website to apply Apply Now Apply On Company Site Save this job Save this job Data Scientist jobs in Atlanta, GA Jobs at Delta in Atlanta, GA Data Scientist salaries in Atlanta, GA Company Info Follow Get job updates from Delta Delta 4,193 reviews We’ve been connecting people since our first passenger flight in 1929. Since then, we’ve been steadily climbing toward our goal of being ... Let employers find you Thousands of employers search for candidates on Indeed Upload your resume 
 
